September 9 at 8:32 PM ·

This week we're starting a new program at Ada Bulldogs called Deputy Carl's Unsung Heroes. We want to recognize the students that are doing great things, whether at school, at home, or in the community! Send me a message with the good things your students are doing, big or small, and I'll choose some to post on the page. If your student gets a shoutout on my page, they can come see me at school for a free candy bar! Let's spread some positivity and recognize those that are doing great things around us. We'll include the virtual kids in this too and figure out how to get them their candy bar.

post_text:
We are excited to start school on Monday! Reminder regarding paying school fees online, you can access PayschoolsCentral by going to the school website: adabulldogs.org. Click the arrow next to the purple "Food Service" box. The PaySchoolsCentral link will come up. After selecting, choose register if you have not used this feature before. You will need your child's student ID number for registration which can be found in ProgressBook or by contact the school office. When paying school fees, remember there is a credit card option which charges a percentage fee or an electronic check option which is a flat rate regardless of the amount. Also, anyone who would prefer to send a check directly to the high school or elementary office through the mail or to deliver the payment in person can do so.

Additionally, if you have not had a chance to watch the Virtual Open House videos, please make sure to visit https://www.adabulldogs.org/News/openhouse20 to meet your teachers!

Everyone have a great weekend, we'll see you Monday, and GO BULLDOGS!

post_text:
Prior to participating in athletics each student is required to have a valid physical. Once completed the physical is good for 13 months. This year physicals are still required in Ohio and each student must have a valid physical on file prior to the first day of practice (August 1st for fall sports).

In addition to your family doctor, the offices listed below will schedule physical appointments:
Mercy Health - Defiance Hospital Family Medicine
604 West North Avenue
419-634-0431

Griffin Chiropractic
122 S Main St.
419-634-9897

July 20 at 9:10 PM ·

ADA MARCHING BAND AND VARSITY SINGER PARENTS! This Friday, your marching band student will be bringing home an envelope of Bulldog Cards (our discount card fundraiser) to sell. On Monday, your Varsity Singer members will be bringing theirs home. If students are in both groups, they will only receive 1 envelope. PLEASE read the front of the envelope AND the note enclosed. We are only asking each student to sell 8 cards. THESE ARE VERY POPULAR AND EASY TO SELL! The cards are $10 each. PLLLLEEEEASE ask your child about these on Friday or Monday.

VARSITY SINGER FAMILIES, on Monday, your student will also receive an Ada Varsity Singer spirit pack form. THESE MUST BE TURNED IN TO ARLENE ALLISON BY AUG.1. These are TOTALLY optional, but a chance for family and friends to get Varsity Singer shirts or sweatshirts for this year. PLLLLEEEEASE ask your student for this form on Monday.

Thanks All!!!!

post_text: We are pleased to announce a public hotspot in Ada where the public can get online. We know how important it is for you to be able to access reliable, high-speed Internet. The hotspot is located in our south parking lot. We want everyone to stay in their vehicles while accessing the hotspots. Social distancing doesn’t stop in the parking lot! post_text:
CAN YOU HELP?
I’m looking for multiple sources to provide/donate a total of 500 hand made masks. 200 are covered from one source, 100 most likely from another. The group for which I’m asking are mental health providers and/or volunteers in Allen, Auglaize, and Hardin Counties. These are folks supporting others with mental heath and social support needs, such as those working in crisis shelters, homeless shelters, social services crisis workers, etc. Many of these folks serve our Ada students and families. It is becoming more essential than ever to serve those with mental health concerns, the marginalized, and some of the most challenged populations in our counties. Please message us on our FB messenger if you have any you can donate now or can create, acquire fairly quickly, etc. Thank you in advance.

Real messages recently received by a teacher from students:

"Just wanted to see how you were doing. I miss your class and miss talking to you."

"I never thought I would say this but I miss school and want to go back 😂"

"I never realized how much easier it is learning in a classroom."

I saw someone post recently that this event will lead us to realize how unnecessary school BUILDINGS are. I strongly believe the exact opposite. Never underestimate the power and importance of human connection. I know the Ada Bulldog staff won’t.

Miss you, Bulldog students!💜💛💜

I've ben asked to share this information from the American Red Cross, during this difficult time. They can really use people who are able, to help in a variety of ways. Please read below and thoughtfully consider if you are able to assist. The Red Cross does amazing work in all kinds of disasters and is the heart of blood supply across our country.

A quick community service announcement here (please share!!)... The American Red Cross is looking for local volunteers throughout Ohio that would be willing to help at blood drives and local disasters. In addition, we are also looking for 'HELP FROM HOME" volunteers to help with volunteer support. All required training and resources will be
provided. For more info, send an email to volunteerohio@redcross.org or visit our volunteer website at
www.redcross.org/volunteer .... Blood Donors are also needed in every area - visit redcrossblood.org to find the closest donation site near you to schedule an appointment! Thanks in advance for your consideration..

post_text:
Our awesome Ada Library is missing us all. They shared this info with our teachers, and we want to share it with you all. A great idea for everyone who wants to “travel” via a great read.

“Students can check out books digitally from the Ohio Digital Library even if they do not have a library card.” One of our teachers said, “We have successfully checked things out and it’s given us new things to read, listen to, etc.”

Here’s the link: https://ohdbks.overdrive.com. Chloe has also posted a how-to video for new users of the system on the library's Facebook page if anyone needs help.

Thank you Ada Library folks! We miss you!!! #bulldogsread #ohtheplacesyouwillgo

📺📝📚 Working together to support Ohio's students!

Beginning Monday, March 30, Ohio’s eight PBS stations will air grade-level appropriate, standards-based programs for students as part of their new #LearnAtHome initiative. Check your local listings for the full schedule.

The educational teams at each station will provide additional resources related to the new programming schedule.

Visit http://pbslearningmedia.org to access free online resources for educators and students.

The Ohio Broadcast Educational Media Commission shares more details here: https://broadcast.ohio.gov/Portals/0/Images/ProjectSpotlight/OhioPublicBroadcastersUnite_NewsRelease_3_26_2020.pdf

#InThisTogetherOhio #OhioEd

ATTENTION: Ada is a community where people step up, begging for ways to help when tough times happen. Here’s a way many may be able to help.

The Red Cross has had to cancel many blood drives that were scheduled on college campuses and now public school campuses. This is not a time to have a blood shortage (there’s never a time where that’s acceptable).

Thus, I wanted to share info from the Red Cross about a local blood drive coming up soon.

Ada Visiting Nurses on 3/23/2020 from 11:30 am -5:30 pm
1200 S. Main
Ada, OHIO 45810

Please call Mary Hackworth to sign up for an appointment, 419-604-8569. She can answer any questions you may have as well.

post_text:
The ONU Cheerleaders will be hosting a Youth Cheerleading Clinic where participants will learn chants, jumps, basic stunting and tumbling techniques, and will perform with the ONU Cheerleaders at halftime. Clinic is $35 per person. Cost of the clinic includes a pizza lunch, a t-shirt, and entrance for the participant to the basketball game. Optional Spirit Pack, including a white bow, a pair of orange pompoms, and two temporary tattoos, is available for an additional $10.

To register please complete the linked registration form at https://payment.onu.edu/C21185_ustores/web/classic/store_main.jsp?STOREID=154. Please note that all participants must register before the clinic. Payment can be made using a credit card or web check at the time of registration or with cash due upon arrival. Please direct any questions to k-mchugh@onu.edu.

We hope that your cheerleader will be able to join us! Go Bears!

post_text: Kindergarten has been learning about high and low sounds and today, Mrs. Klingler's class learned how the size of an instrument affects how high or low of a sound it makes. The kids worked together by playing and comparing sizes to place their Boomwhacker instruments in order from low to high. They did a great job connecting music with science!

post_text: Ada HS’s Varsity Singers, a competition show choir, will be competing at Findlay HS, tomorrow (January 25) at 11 AM, at the Findlay High School auditorium. Their 2020 show is a caffeinated wonder, centered around the world of work and Mrs. Skilliter’s favorite...COFFEE!!!There is an admission to cover tournament costs, and you can watch as many teams as you like, before and after the 11:00 VS performance. This is their closest tournament, so it’s a golden opportunity to see them live. The students feed off the energy of the crowd, so let’s pack the auditorium and help them bring home more hardware for our school. Good luck, VS!!! We love you a “latte.”

post_text: In the spirit of giving during the holiday season, the fifth grade students have been collecting items (i.e. coloring books, crayons, activity books) to be donated to a pediatric wing at a local hospital. We know that children of all ages may find themselves needing medical care this Christmas and we thought it would be nice to offer them some holiday cheer. These items will also be donated in memory of Taylor Carder. Taylor's mom, Kelly Carder, is an aide in our building. She tragically lost her daughter, Taylor, in a car accident 6 years ago. Taylor was a beautiful young girl who touched so many lives. We hope that our students’ generosity will bring smiles to children in the hospital while helping to keep Taylor’s memory alive.

post_text:
The elementary school held a door decorating contest this week. Here's the results:

Grades K-2 grand prize winner: Mrs. Kosier (K)
Grades 3-5 grand prize winner: Mrs. Burris (5)

Grade K winner: Mrs. Kosier
Grade 1 winner: Mrs. Ludwig
Grade 2 winner: Mrs. Preston
Grade 3 winner: Miss Daniels
Grade 4 winner: Mrs. Rieman
Grade 5 winner: Mrs. Burris
Other winner: Mrs. Jochims

Grand prize winners received donuts and chocolate milk this morning and grade level winners received candy canes.

Thank you to our judges, Mayor Dave Retterer, Fred Steiner and Rhett Grant!

Pictures coming soon!

post_text: Tonight our Tech Wizards after school STEM program presented their skills to their families. Students have learned to code through Sphero robots and Parrot drones. Thank you to Mark Light and the OSU 4H Extension Office and Ada STEM teacher Mr. Jeff Hunt for running this amazing program with our 4-6 students.
